				<h1>Sarvagna on sleeping</h1>
				
					<p>I bought a copy of <em>Sarvagnana VachanagaLu</em>; a collection of >1000 kannada triplets by 12AD(?) poet-saint Sarvagna. An appropriate &#8216;vachana&#8217; for the moment <br />
<tt><br />
vadane yogige holla | badane rogige holla |<br />
kadanavadu holla nereyali, niddege |<br />
tudigatte holla sarvagna<br />
</tt><br />
<strong>Translation</strong>:<tt><br />
a fair maiden is bad for a hermit | so is a brinjal for the unwell |<br />
undesirable is bickering with the neighbour and |<br />
so is sleeping on the edge of a platform  </tt> :)<br />
Forgive my crude translation. Its a <strong>joy</strong> to read the <em>vachanas</em> in kannada. </p>


